<br>
Just to repeat my recurring theme, you can prove yourself right if you're backing the right thing with facts and evidence.  I do not think everyone has 'parts of the truth' and I believe masses of people can be wrong.  I don't think anyone is going to hell, or heaven for that matter.  There is no evidence either of those places exist.  I think those fundies who obsess over their own righteousness and your inadequacy are in hell right here already.  <br>
<br>
What you are is a very nice lady.  You don’t want others to be left out or excluded, so you incorporate a way into your beliefs to save them.  Because your theology is as wrong and fallaciously based as theirs, however, you can no more prove yourself right than they can.<br>
<br>
Who is right?  Agnostics, Atheists and Deists.<br>
<br>
Why?  They either cannot be disproven or are supported by the facts.  Everyone else (except maybe Buddhists) is in breach of material facts to the contrary.<br>
<br>
The result is that they have a vested interest in you being proven wrong or their beliefs are rendered invalid.  This is the mechanism of all religious persecution.  It may be to oppress you and steal your goods, or convert you and increase their ranks, or just plain old kill you, but that is the mechanism by which they devalue your rights to accomplish their ends.<br>
<br>
Religion sucks.<br>
